Purchased Today: Dragon Quest 11 S - Echoes of an Elusive Age
Platform: Nintendo Switch
——-
I’ve been looking forward to this game for a while now, and now that means there is only one last game that hasn’t been released since first announcement of the Switch back in January 2017 (I’m looking at you Shin Megami Tensei V).i don’t know if I have ever mentioned it on this account, but Dragon Warrior was the first JRPG I ever played; I played the first one, the third one, and that was it for the entire franchise for me until I played Dragon Quest Builders. I’m super excited to return to a series that I haven’t played since I was a child, and I loved the demo so I know I’m going to love this game, the only conflict I see is if I’m ever going to say aside Dragon Quest Builders 2 so that I can play other games. Maybe at some point, I still need to try out Darksiders, and Link’s Awakening. I have to many games and only so much time in the day to play Dragon Quest Builders 2.
——-

caption.text:
A terceira temporada de Apex Legends começa em 1º de outubro. Respawn Entertainment e  Electronic Arts divulgaram o trailer de lançamento com a seguinte descrição: "Estes são os Confins do Mundo, um novo mapa de Apex Legends onde calor escaldante e frio químico colidem. Junte-se ao nosso elenco de Lendas, incluindo a estreia de Crypto, no transporte enquanto são levados do planeta Solace até os Confins do Mundo no planeta Talos." Até 1º de outubro 🙋

caption.text:
Today's video game vinyl OST feature is Sayonara Wild Hearts! The PAX West Red Bull Challenge Mode Limited Edition 7" single, specifically! Very special thanks to the generous @adoniamerritt and @obliviouskev for getting and sending this to me ❤️
Developed by @simogogames , published by @annapurnainteractive, distributed by @iam8bit and composed and performed by Daniel Olsén, Linnea Olssen and Jonathan Eng, a visually stunning game that's described as "a pop album video game", mixing several types of gameplay into another indie masterpiece!
This is only the second 7" single I have in my collection and I've been so excited to finally listen to it since I first saw the E3 trailer!

caption.text:
Behold the Ultra-Rare PC Engine LT: Gaming Holy Grail!!! 😻😻 Have you seen this before? It looks awesome!! .
Source: https://ja.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/PCエンジンLT
.
Feast your eyes on the PC Engine LT. The PC Engine was the Japanese name for what, in the US, was called the Turbo GrafX 16. There were many variants on the PC engine hardware, including two portable versions: The PC Engine GT (Turbo Express in the US) and the PC Engine LT.

The PC Engine LT ( PCエンジンLT ) is a "portable" laptop variant of the PC Engine, released exclusively in Japan in December 1991.

The PC Engine LT is essentially a PC Engine with a built-in flip-up screen and built in speaker, negating the need to link up the console to a television. Unlike the PC Engine GT (the older, more portable unit), however, the LT uses a power supply and is built with a similar form factor as the original PC Engine, allowing it to be linked up, for example to a CD-ROM². .

caption.text:
Silent Hill 2 saiu em 2001 para o PS2 pela Konami, pegou tudo que o primeiro título tinha de bom/assustador e melhorou de uma forma nunca antes vista em um jogo. O mais curioso aqui são os diversos finais que podemos conseguir. No total são 3 finais e um quarto dando uma complementada no enredo todo. No entanto há um quinto final que quebra toda a tensão e medo do jogo. Após realizar os três primeiros finais, existe um item chamado Dog Key que te dá acesso para uma torre de comando e mostra que um pequeno cachorro da raça shiba estava tramando tudo o tempo todo. Esse é um dos finais mais engraçados dos jogos e fica ainda melhor por estar em um jogo onde a temática de terror é tão forte.
